snippet.textDisplay:
Thumbs up if you’re listening to it on loop. Every time you listen to this masterpiece, you’ll notice more nuances. You’ll notice that little riff which you had missed earlier, one stanza will take on a whole new meaning, the singer’s voice will seem that much more emotional at the end of that line.
Listening to a song is much like reading a book. The first time you read it, it thrills you and you have a clear idea of what the author wanted to say. But read it again and again and you notice every shade and subtle ideas the author put in. That takes your appreciation of the book to a whole new level. and so is the case with songs.
Love from India... :)

snippet.textDisplay:
This song has 2 components : lyrics and musical score. For the lyrics on should get to understand Sufi thinking. Sufism is based on love of the creator.The music was always Indian classical but recently the new genre is fusion. The deft combination of classical with western is electrifying. The song is in a dialect of Urdu from the Awadh part of north around Delhi. Coke Studio is a good platform to hear the genius of Abida Praveen.
Finally music should bind people not destroy them.
Let the music play on play on!
